headline: Goldman Sachs shuffles U.S. Utilities: 2 stocks upgraded, 1 lowered to Sell
summary: Investing.com -- Goldman Sachs made several adjustments to its U.S. utilities coverage, upgrading Duke Energy (NYSE:DUK) and Ameren (NYSE:AEE) while cutting WEC Energy (NYSE:WEC) to a Sell, citing valuation concerns and earnings growth risks.
